Appium Device Farm Plugin Setup Guide

1. Prerequisites
Appium Version 2.0.0 Make sure you have Appium version 2.0.0 installed on your system.
npm install -g appium@2.0.0-beta.43
Node.js: Appium is built on Node.js so you need to have Node.js installed.

2. Installing the Appium Device Farm Plugin
 Step 1: The Appium Device Farm Plugin can be installed using Appium's plugin CLI
  appium plugin install --source=npm appium-device-farm
 Step 2: Install the Appium Dashboard Plugin
  Similarly install the Appium Dashboard Plugin using the following command:
  appium plugin install --source=npm appium-dashboard

3. Activating the Device Farm Plugin Using Command Line Arguments
appium server -ka 800 --use-plugins=device-farm,appium-dashboard -pa /wd/hub --plugin-device-farm-platform=android

4. Navigate to localhost:4723/device-farm once the appium server is started.
